17/02/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu called on Wednesday (16 February) for timely completion of trials in the District Court for Serious Crimes, saying that "delayed justice is a denied justice".
As chairman of the High Judicial Council, Moisiu participated in the Court's annual meeting dedicated to analysing the work of the institution.
Also Wednesday, Public Order Minister Igli Toska admitted problems with the police vigilance system at the regional level, following several recent incidents related to attempts by prisoners to escape in Tirana and Shkodra.
One fugitive remains at large.
(Albanian News - 17/02/05)
